cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY. 

The paper focuses on a mobile robot performing visual recognition tasks, which suggests the primary category of Robotics (cs.RO). The use of convolutional networks and classifiers for semantic mapping and categorization suggests Computer Vision (cs.CV) as a likely sub-category. The incorporation of Bayesian filtering and temporal coherence suggests Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as another possible sub-category. The use of machine learning techniques for classification suggests Machine Learning (cs.LG) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the use of the semantic map to modulate the robot's behavior during navigation tasks suggests Systems and Control (cs.SY) as a possible sub-category.
